result.execSummary:
The defendant Mickey J Frank Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Possession of Drug Paraphernalia. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Called at 3:59 PM. Mickey Frank Jr. appears in person and in custody with attorney David Penn. State appears by Charles Simono. State - resolved - amend #1 to first offense possession of THC contrary to 961.41(3g)(e) - $1000 fine plus costs and surhcarge, amend #2 to county ordinance possession of drug paraphanalia with $500 fine plus costs. Penn and Frank agree. Court amends count #2 to county ordinance possession of drug paraphanalia - pleads NC - finds G - fine of $500.00 plus costs totalling $834.50 - 60 DTP/CO. Court amends count #1 to first offense possession of THC contrary to 961.41(3g)(e) - reads new charge and penalty. Frank pleads NC to amended count #1. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation. Penn - follow joint recommendation. Frank withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - fine of $1000 plus costs and surcharges totalling $2658.00 - 60 DTP/CO, right to appeal, adjourned.
